Possible values are from 0 to 20; the default for plain number and percent formatting is 0; the default for currency formatting is the number of minor unit digits provided by the ISO 4217 currency code list (2 if the list doesn't provide that information).

values.description: When filtering is enabled, filterBy decides which field or fields (comma separated) to search against.

values.name: filterMode
values.description: Mode for filtering valid values are "lenient" and "strict". Default is lenient.

values.name: filterPlaceholder

values.name: filterInputAutoFocus
values.description: Determines whether the filter input should be automatically focused when the component is rendered.

values.name: propagateSelectionUp
values.description: Whether checkbox selections propagate to ancestor nodes.

values.name: resetFilterOnHide

values.name: virtualScroll

values.name: virtualScrollItemSize

values.name: autofocus

TreeTable.description: TreeTable is used to display hierarchical data in tabular format.

props.description: Defines the input properties of the component.

values.name: dt
values.description: Defines scoped design tokens of the component.

values.name: pt
values.description: Used to pass attributes to DOM elements inside the component.

values.name: ptOptions
values.description: Used to configure passthrough(pt) options of the component.

values.name: columns
values.description: An array of objects to represent dynamic columns.

values.name: styleClass
values.description: Style class of the component.

values.name: tableStyle
values.description: Inline style of the table.

values.name: tableStyleClass
values.description: Style class of the table.

values.name: autoLayout
values.description: Whether the cell widths scale according to their content or not.

values.name: lazy
values.description: Defines if data is loaded and interacted with in lazy manner.

values.name: lazyLoadOnInit
values.description: Whether to call lazy loading on initialization.

values.name: paginator
values.description: When specified as true, enables the pagination.

values.name: rows
values.description: Number of rows to display per page.

values.name: first
values.description: Index of the first row to be displayed.

values.name: pageLinks
values.description: Number of page links to display in paginator.

values.name: rowsPerPageOptions
values.description: Array of integer/object values to display inside rows per page dropdown of paginator

values.name: alwaysShowPaginator
values.description: Whether to show it even there is only one page.

values.name: paginatorPosition
values.description: Position of the paginator.

values.name: paginatorStyleClass
values.description: Custom style class for paginator

values.name: paginatorDropdownAppendTo
values.description: Target element to attach the paginator dropdown overlay, valid values are "body" or a local ng-template variable of another element (note: use binding with brackets for template variables, e.g. [appendTo]="mydiv" for a div element having #mydiv as variable name).

values.name: currentPageReportTemplate
values.description: Template of the current page report element. Available placeholders are {currentPage},{totalPages},{rows},{first},{last} and {totalRecords}

values.name: showCurrentPageReport
values.description: Whether to display current page report.

values.name: showJumpToPageDropdown
values.description: Whether to display a dropdown to navigate to any page.

values.name: showFirstLastIcon
values.description: When enabled, icons are displayed on paginator to go first and last page.

values.name: showPageLinks
values.description: Whether to show page links.

values.name: defaultSortOrder
values.description: Sort order to use when an unsorted column gets sorted by user interaction.

values.name: sortMode
values.description: Defines whether sorting works on single column or on multiple columns.

values.name: resetPageOnSort
values.description: When true, resets paginator to first page after sorting.

values.name: customSort
values.description: Whether to use the default sorting or a custom one using sortFunction.

values.name: selectionMode
values.description: Specifies the selection mode, valid values are "single" and "multiple".

values.name: contextMenuSelection
values.description: Selected row with a context menu.

values.name: contextMenuSelectionMode
values.description: Mode of the contet menu selection.

values.name: dataKey
values.description: A property to uniquely identify a record in data.

values.name: metaKeySelection
values.description: Defines whether metaKey is should be considered for the selection. On touch enabled devices, metaKeySelection is turned off automatically.

values.name: compareSelectionBy
values.description: Algorithm to define if a row is selected, valid values are "equals" that compares by reference and "deepEquals" that compares all fields.

values.name: rowHover
values.description: Adds hover effect to rows without the need for selectionMode.

values.name: loading
values.description: Displays a loader to indicate data load is in progress.

values.name: loadingIcon
values.description: The icon to show while indicating data load is in progress.

values.name: showLoader
values.description: Whether to show the loading mask when loading property is true.

values.name: scrollable
values.description: When specified, enables horizontal and/or vertical scrolling.

values.name: scrollHeight
values.description: Height of the scroll viewport in fixed pixels or the "flex" keyword for a dynamic size.

values.name: virtualScroll
values.description: Whether the data should be loaded on demand during scroll.

values.name: virtualScrollItemSize
values.description: Height of a row to use in calculations of virtual scrolling.

values.name: virtualScrollOptions
values.description: Whether to use the scroller feature. The properties of scroller component can be used like an object in it.

values.name: virtualScrollDelay
values.description: The delay (in milliseconds) before triggering the virtual scroll. This determines the time gap between the user's scroll action and the actual rendering of the next set of items in the virtual scroll.

values.name: frozenWidth
values.description: Width of the frozen columns container.

values.name: frozenColumns
values.description: An array of objects to represent dynamic columns that are frozen.

values.name: resizableColumns
values.description: When enabled, columns can be resized using drag and drop.

values.name: columnResizeMode
values.description: Defines whether the overall table width should change on column resize, valid values are "fit" and "expand".

values.name: reorderableColumns
values.description: When enabled, columns can be reordered using drag and drop.

values.name: contextMenu
values.description: Local ng-template varilable of a ContextMenu.

values.name: rowTrackBy
values.description: Function to optimize the dom operations by delegating to ngForTrackBy, default algorithm checks for object identity.

values.name: filters
values.description: An array of FilterMetadata objects to provide external filters.

values.name: globalFilterFields
values.description: An array of fields as string to use in global filtering.

values.name: filterDelay
values.description: Delay in milliseconds before filtering the data.

values.name: filterMode
values.description: Mode for filtering valid values are "lenient" and "strict". Default is lenient.

values.name: filterLocale
values.description: Locale to use in filtering. The default locale is the host environment's current locale.

values.name: paginatorLocale
values.description: Locale to be used in paginator formatting.

values.name: totalRecords
values.description: Number of total records, defaults to length of value when not defined.

values.name: sortField
values.description: Name of the field to sort data by default.

values.name: sortOrder
values.description: Order to sort when default sorting is enabled.

values.name: multiSortMeta
values.description: An array of SortMeta objects to sort the data by default in multiple sort mode.

values.name: selection
values.description: Selected row in single mode or an array of values in multiple mode.

values.name: value
values.description: An array of objects to display.

values.name: virtualRowHeight
values.description: Indicates the height of rows to be scrolled.

values.name: selectionKeys
values.description: A map of keys to control the selection state.

values.name: showGridlines
values.description: Whether to show grid lines between cells.

values.description: Callback to invoke on selected node change.

values.description: Callback to invoke on context menu selection change.

values.description: Callback to invoke when data is filtered.

values.name: onNodeExpand
values.description: Callback to invoke when a node is expanded.

values.name: onNodeCollapse
values.description: Callback to invoke when a node is collapsed.

values.name: onPage
values.description: Callback to invoke when pagination occurs.

values.name: onSort
values.description: Callback to invoke when a column gets sorted.

values.name: onLazyLoad
values.description: Callback to invoke when paging, sorting or filtering happens in lazy mode.

values.name: sortFunction
values.description: An event emitter to invoke on custom sorting, refer to sorting section for details.

values.name: onColResize
values.description: Callback to invoke when a column is resized.

values.name: onColReorder
values.description: Callback to invoke when a column is reordered.

values.name: onNodeSelect
values.description: Callback to invoke when a node is selected.

values.name: onNodeUnselect
values.description: Callback to invoke when a node is unselected.

values.description: Callback to invoke when a node is selected with right click.

values.description: Callback to invoke when state of header checkbox changes.

values.description: Callback to invoke when a cell switches to edit mode.

values.description: Callback to invoke when cell edit is completed.

values.description: Callback to invoke when cell edit is cancelled with escape key.

values.description: Callback to invoke when selectionKeys are changed.

values.description: Scrolls to given index when using virtual scroll.
